WEBVTT

00:03.000 --> 00:05.878
<i>One of the reasons Turk and I
<i>are so popular around here</i></i>

00:05.960 --> 00:07.996
<i>is we love helping</i>
<i>our fellow doctors.</i>

00:08.080 --> 00:11.390
- Hey, Hooch.
- That's my name. Don't wear it out.

00:11.480 --> 00:14.358
Classic Hooch. Even though
I'm not gonna be paid,

00:14.440 --> 00:17.876
I'll cover your shift
so you can do Mr Schindler's endoscopy.

00:17.960 --> 00:20.235
I'll cross-cover Dr Turner's patients

00:20.320 --> 00:22.550
so Turner can assist you
on the procedure.

00:22.640 --> 00:24.835
Why are you going
through so much trouble?

00:24.920 --> 00:27.309
Who's doing the endoscopy
on Mr Schindler?

00:27.400 --> 00:29.436
- Turner and Hooch!
- Turner and Hooch!

00:30.720 --> 00:32.631
All right!

00:32.720 --> 00:34.517
Were you just Hooch?

00:34.600 --> 00:36.238
Everyone hates you guys.

00:36.320 --> 00:39.073
- Hooch.
- Hooch is crazy!

00:39.160 --> 00:42.357
<i>As much as Hooch loved us, it was</i>
<i>even better to see Turk happy.</i>

00:42.440 --> 00:46.399
<i>He and Carla started couples therapy,</i>
<i>and I'm not sure he was enjoying it.</i>

00:47.800 --> 00:49.950
Carla says you cry after you orgasm.

00:50.040 --> 00:53.032
- Would you like to talk about that?
- No, not really.

00:54.240 --> 00:56.708
<i>I decided to help their marriage</i>
<i>by moving out,</i>

00:56.800 --> 01:00.429
<i>partly because Carla and I accidentally</i>
<i>kissed and messed things up,</i>

01:00.520 --> 01:04.069
<i>but mostly because it was time.</i>
<i>Finding an apartment has not been easy.</i>

01:04.160 --> 01:05.798
I'm so sorry about your father.

01:05.880 --> 01:08.030
I'm sure he lived a wonderful life

01:08.120 --> 01:11.112
at 14 Maple Drive, apartment 4B.

01:11.200 --> 01:14.272
Was he lucky enough to enjoy
a washer and dryer in his unit

01:14.360 --> 01:16.555
while he was alive?

01:17.560 --> 01:19.357
Ever mention any hot neighbours?

01:21.520 --> 01:23.476
What are you doing
in the on-call room?

01:23.560 --> 01:24.549
Nothing.

01:24.640 --> 01:26.358
- I gotta go.
- OK.

01:27.040 --> 01:29.474
<i>Thankfully, Turk got over the kissing.</i>

01:29.560 --> 01:32.393
<i>There's a weird new thing he does</i>
<i>when he says goodbye.</i>

01:32.480 --> 01:33.959
OK, I'll see you around.

01:35.360 --> 01:36.759
Peace, homey.

01:37.880 --> 01:40.952
Do you guys think that Clarissa
is more attractive than me?

01:41.040 --> 01:42.029
Yes.

01:43.080 --> 01:44.638
Who's Clarissa?

01:44.720 --> 01:47.029
The short, balding woman
in the pharmacy.

01:47.120 --> 01:48.712
Oh, then, definitely yes.

01:48.800 --> 01:51.633
She just got engaged,
bad combover and all.

01:51.720 --> 01:54.632
She beats you to the altar,
time to hang up the ovaries.

01:54.720 --> 01:57.996
Too mean. How am I supposed
to meet a guy working in this place?

01:58.080 --> 01:59.638
Are the guys here that bad?

02:01.520 --> 02:03.875
Twelve minutes door to door!

02:03.960 --> 02:06.110
That's a personal best, suckos!

02:08.440 --> 02:10.431
Nurse, suction.

02:10.520 --> 02:12.875
The patient's not even here yet.

02:13.000 --> 02:13.989
I know.

02:15.240 --> 02:18.755
I just wish once a cute, thoughtful guy
would walk through the door.

02:21.520 --> 02:23.511
Can I get help?
My neighbour fainted.

02:23.600 --> 02:26.558
She doesn't like ambulances,
so I brought her in myself.

02:26.640 --> 02:28.870
Let me take this one.
You've got a phone call.

02:28.960 --> 02:31.633
- I'll call them back.
- Your mom died.

02:31.720 --> 02:33.119
What?

02:33.880 --> 02:36.678
Her mom's fine. It's just
a little running joke we have.

02:36.760 --> 02:39.228
She'll be laughing later.
Gotcha, Jenny!

02:40.560 --> 02:42.551
Dead mom joke's always funny.

